Orascom Telecom of Egypt Asks for $350 Million Loan, Alam Says

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-05-29T08:08:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-29/orascom-telecom-of-egypt-asks-for-350-million-loan-alam-says.html
Orascom Telecom Holding SAE (ORTE)  has
requested a $350 million loan from Egyptian banks to refinance
the debt of a new company it established,  Al Alam Al Youm 
reported, citing unidentified banking officials.  Orascom is negotiating with banks including  Commercial
International Bank Egypt SAE (COMI) , National Societe Generale Bank and
HSBC Holdings Plc to obtain the loan for the company it formed
to hold assets not included in its merger with  VimpelCom Ltd. (VIP) ,
the Cairo-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mahmoud Kassem at 
 mkassem1@bloomberg.net . 